parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line quick disconnect can cause fuel to leak under high pressure, potentially leading to a fire, crash, and serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel sprays out of the coupling
fuel leaks onto the engine and rider's leg
heavy gasoline odor
excessive fuel consumption
severe gasoline leak
hesitation when accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel scheduling problem can cause the vehicle to hesitate severely when accelerating from a stop, leading to dangerous situations when pulling out into traffic.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates severely when accelerating from a stop
especially in hot weather conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Plastic Fuel Line Quick Disconnect Coupling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked plastic fuel line quick disconnect coupling can cause fuel to leak from the engine compartment, leading to a high risk of fire and injury.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the engine compartment
fuel sprays out in a fine mist
fuel leaks from the right side of the engine above the valve cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear drive can cause the motorcycle to become extremely unstable, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear end of the motorcycle feels unstable
fluid leaking from the rear drive
the rear wheel appears to be about to fall off
the motorcycle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tire tread from the tire base can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially on motorcycles.
symptoms: The tire tread separates from the tire base
leading to loss of traction and control
especially at high speeds or in wet conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Road Defects and Lack of Signage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Road defects, such as recessed metal joints, can cause accidents and injuries, especially for motorcyclists, who may lose control of their vehicle.
symptoms: Loss of control
accidents
and injuries due to road defects
especially in wet conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear ABS system can cause loss of traction and stability, leading to accidents, especially during heavy braking or slippery road conditions.
symptoms: ABS brake lights come on
rear ABS system fails to function
front ABS system still works
slowing down to stop triggers the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in extended stopping distances, accidents, or even complete brake failure.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
spongy brake pedal
reduced brake performance
cracked brake lines.
